narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes definitely (if you have strong motivation and enough time to work additional hours).

With Professor Barbeito, we studied etching, screen print, wood cut, and collograph, and how to combine the techniques. Making the prints was fun. Printmaking is an important skill for a visual artist. That said, if you are looking for a rigorous technical course or an in-depth exploration of the techniques, this course is not for you.
Definitely! A great introduction and printmaking is really great!
